Program: Great Lives
Title: Rachel Johnson on Ottoline Morrell
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b05qgch9
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 17 Apr 2015
Rachel Johnson author and journalist champions the life of Ottoline Morrell. The Bloomsbury hostess, a mistress, a dominant figure in the arts without being an artist herself was often mocked and ridiculed. Rachel tells Matthew Parris why her extraordinary life was a great life. They are also joined by author and one of Lady Ottoline's biographers Miranda Seymour. Producer : Perminder Khatkar. Show less